<title>SPAIN: Telefonica says CTC, VTR talks &quot;advanced&quot;.</title>
<headline>Telefonica says CTC, VTR talks &quot;advanced&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1997-06-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Spain's Telefonica de Espana, which controls Chilean telephone operator CTC, said on Monday talks for a CTC merger with Chilean rival VTR were advanced.</p>
<p>&quot;Negotiations are in advanced stages,&quot; a spokesman said.</p>
<p>Press reports on Monday cited Telefonica director general Javier Revuelta in New York saying VTR, controlled by the Luksic group and SBC Communications Inc, would merge with CTC.</p>
<p>Telefonica could not confirm his comments.</p>
<p>Under the deal, Luksic would buy into Telefonica Chile Holding, the group which controls the 43.62 percent stake of CTC that gives management control, and SBC would sell its VTR stake, financial daily Expansion said.</p>
<p>--Madrid Newsroom +34 1 585 2167</p>
